Overview
GigShield embeds AI/ML at three critical points in the platform:
ModulePurposeModel TypeRisk ScoringCalculate personalized weekly premiumXGBoost (Gradient Boosted Trees)Disruption ForecastingPredict next week's disruption probabilityFacebook Prophet (Time Series)Fraud DetectionDetect anomalous or fake claimsIsolation Forest + Rule Engine
All ML models are served via a FastAPI microservice (Python), called by the Node.js backend.

Module 1: Dynamic Risk Scoring (Premium Calculation)
Goal
Generate a risk_score (0.8 – 2.0) for each worker that feeds directly into the premium formula.
Model Type
XGBoost / LightGBM — chosen for tabular data, handles missing values, fast inference
Input Features
FeatureSourceExamplezone_disruption_freq_3yrHistorical IMD + CPCB data42 events/year in Tambaramzone_flood_risk_indexIMD climate zone data0.85 (high flood zone)month_of_yearCalendar10 (October = monsoon)platform_typeOnboardingfood_deliveryavg_daily_hoursWorker declaration10 hoursyears_on_platformMock platform API2.5 yearshistorical_claim_rateGigShield DB (after launch)0 for new workers
Output
json{
  "worker_id": "W-10042",
  "risk_score": 1.38,
  "risk_tier": "HIGH",
  "recommended_coverage_tier": "Standard",
  "confidence": 0.87
}
Training Data

IMD historical weather data (2020–2025) per district
CPCB AQI historical records per city
Synthetic worker profiles (for MVP phase — 10,000 generated records)
Real data to be incorporated post-launch via feedback loop


Module 2: Disruption Forecasting (Predictive Pricing)
Goal
Forecast the probability of a disruptive event in the next 7 days for each operating zone. Used to:

Dynamically adjust next week's premium on renewal day (Monday)
Show insurer a predictive claims exposure view

Model Type
Facebook Prophet — excellent for seasonal patterns (monsoon cycles), holiday effects (bandh-prone periods)
Input

3-year daily weather history per zone (temperature, rainfall, AQI)
Indian public holiday calendar (potential social disruption dates)
IMD seasonal forecast data

Output
json{
  "zone": "tambaram_chennai",
  "week_starting": "2026-03-23",
  "disruption_probability": 0.72,
  "dominant_risk": "heavy_rain",
  "expected_disruption_days": 2.1,
  "premium_adjustment_factor": 1.18
}
Usage in Platform
Every Sunday night:
  → Forecast model runs for all active zones
  → Premium adjustment factors computed
  → Monday morning auto-renewal uses adjusted premium
  → Workers notified if premium changes > 10%

Module 3: Fraud Detection
Goal
Assign a fraud_score (0.0 – 1.0) to every claim. High scores trigger review or auto-rejection.
Model Type
Isolation Forest (unsupervised anomaly detection) + Rule-based pre-filter
Input Features
FeatureSignalgps_in_affected_zoneBoolean — is worker's last GPS ping inside disrupted polygon?platform_active_pre_eventWas worker logged in and active 2 hrs before trigger?claim_frequency_7dHow many claims in last 7 days vs. zone peer average?device_id_sharedIs this device linked to multiple worker accounts?upi_account_age_daysVery new UPI account = higher suspiciontime_since_enrollmentBrand new policy + immediate claim = flagpeer_claim_rate_deltaWorker's claim rate vs. peers in same zone
Decision Thresholds
Fraud ScoreAction0.0 – 0.4✅ AUTO APPROVE — payout initiated immediately0.4 – 0.7🟡 APPROVE with monitoring flag — payout proceeds, account watched0.7 – 0.9🔴 QUEUE for human review — payout held up to 4 hours0.9 – 1.0❌ AUTO REJECT — worker notified, fraud score recorded
Output
json{
  "claim_id": "CLM-20045",
  "fraud_score": 0.23,
  "decision": "AUTO_APPROVE",
  "flags": [],
  "processing_time_ms": 340
}

